&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The input is a list of pairs of the form &lt;code&gt;a|b&lt;/code&gt; which defines that &lt;code&gt;b&lt;/code&gt; must not come before &lt;code&gt;a&lt;/code&gt;, an empty line, and then a list of values &lt;code&gt;a,b,c,d&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For each line that is valid for all given &lt;code&gt;a|b&lt;/code&gt; rules, sum the middle number of each list.&lt;/p&gt;
